<p>When we think about word choices in our own writing, itâ€™s important to focus on the choices that give the most bang for the buck.Â  We donâ€™t achieve that by choosing the rarest word or considering how original or interesting our wording may seem to our reader.Â  We acquire deep vocabulary knowledge by reading, above all, and we apply that knowledge by careful revision and (if weâ€™re lucky) a good editor.Â  :)</p>

